            <title>[CASSANDRA-3433] Describe ring is broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3433</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2882&quot; title=&quot;describe_ring should include datacenter/topology information&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2882&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2882&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; broke describe_ring by causing the &apos;endpoints&apos; field to contain the rpc address rather than the listen address. the rpc_address belongs in the &apos;rpc_endpoints&apos; field. Hence the name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
